    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="115"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 111.70H81</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Ambassadors in Great Britain, France, Germany,
                            Austria-Hungary, Italy, and Russia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">Colonel E. M. House</persName>, accompanied by Mrs.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">House</persName>, will sail for Europe December
                    28, S. S. <hi rend="italic">Rotterdam.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>He proceeds at the request of the President and Secretary of State for the
                    purpose of taking information to our ambassadors in order that they may have a
                    more intimate knowledge of this Government’s attitude regarding certain phases
                    of international questions and in order to obtain from them their point of view
                    on these matters.</p>
                <p>Please impress on Foreign Office that <persName>Colonel House</persName> is not
                    on a peace mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
